      "primitive": {
        "comments": "apply(mf, mx) returns Just(f x) when mf is Just(f) and mx is Just(x), and Nothing if either is Nothing. The applicative apply for maybe; threads a function-in-context with a value-in-context. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's (<*>) :: Maybe (a -> b) -> Maybe a -> Maybe b.",
